{
  "stem": "21139.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then we heard through my uncle that he took a train, put on very old clothes, and went to his mother in Wittenberg, in-- that was Aufhausen, a small place where he came from.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he stayed with my grandmother for a number of weeks.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But we knew he was safe and he was hiding there at my grandmother-- grandmother's.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Then when he came home-- and then of course, we found out that, as I mentioned before, that Julius was in Dachau.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we had to wait until they released him.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he-- Julius told us horror stories from Dachau, what transpired there and the people that were tortured.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we had-- he was lucky that they let him go and that we could-- that my parents could arrange for him to leave the country.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From neighbors, non-Jewish neighbors.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Whenever Hitler spoke, my father used to go to the back and they made it loud enough for my father to listen to, to hear, and-- because we not-- we're not allowed to have any radios.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this is how we knew what was going on.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And for a long time, my parents didn't want to realize or didn't want to make arrangements to leave the country.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father always thought since he fought in the First World War, and nothing can happen to him.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were afraid with four small children to go to a new country not knowing the language.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "How does one make a living?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "By the time they decided that-- to want-- that they wanted to leave, it was too late.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They did apply for papers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they had interviews to go to-- to go to Australia.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we never-- it was too late.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were very kind.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
